Two weeks ago we ordered a pizza that was not delivered.  We got a text with picture of the order on steps -- that were not ours.  We walked around the entire block and there was no pizza on any steps in the neighborhood.  That night I spent a total close to 45 minutes dealing with Door Dash who referred me to the LC corporate office.  Corporate told me it would be refunded.  No apology.  And it wasn't refunded.  That Saturday I called the store and was told a manager would call me back.  No one did.  On Monday I called the store again and the manager said he would refund the cost.  No apologies.  And it has been a week and there is no refund on the charge card.  I sent corporate a tweet.  They took my information and told me someone would get back with me.  No one did.  I have now spent well over an hour and a half trying to get back money for something I never received.  Not only was there the pizza on the charge -- there was a delivery fee and a nice tip on top of it.  Basically Door Dash and Little Caesars didn't deliver the product and kept the money.  At first it seemed like a mistake, then incompetence, and now it seems like they are just stealing from customers.
